A compelling game with some serious problems. Calls I'm never notified 
about, penalties dolled out seemlingly at random (penalised for ignoring a 
woman whose neighbors had their TV on too loud, yet also penalised for 
putting out a fire in a construction site, for example.) Clunky and often 
sticky/awkward touch controls imply this was poorly optimised. A tutorial 
which doesn't make clear the function of many items (for example, the 
terminal). Menus which struggle to be responsive and often function in 
arbitrary, confusing ways. All in all, the serious polish issues combined 
with the fact that this is a £5 mobile game with additional DLC, prevent me 
from rating this higher.

Hi,   I would like to give feedback to the game 911 operator.   Firstly I would like to say it is a very interesting game. Thank you.    There are a few points I would like to be considered to increase the excitement of the game.    1. The wait and ignore button the emergency screen are to close and too small, people like me with big thumbs most of the time press the wrong button, if they were maybe side to side one red and another green, that would stand out.    2.the dark red and the dark blue background are nice, if I haven't played the whole day, but having to play more over the black gets really hard to focus, maybe if the background was white, or I as the user where able to choose the colour of the user interface from the settings that would be awesome.   3. I have purchased all extensions packs, but earning 20,000 per game makes it harder to purchase special unit vehicles which are 300,000. If maybe the vehicles where cheaper it would make it more addictive rather than frustrating especially to find out after paying that the vehicles are only unlocked and not bought. At least one vehicle each, would have been good.    4.there are some emergencies that are have 5 suspects, if there was a special units vehicle that had 10 or 15 even 20 crew vehicle, like a swat car, that would be awesome.     Again thank you for an awesome game, if possible to maybe do some of these points to your professionality as developers, I would hope it brings better customers better reviews and make it more interesting to play for longer periods.    Kindest regards   Selim
